{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784254193728369269,"compiled_state":{"alias":"truthful-specified-silverfish","assignee":"","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"b0ac25447203d864463408c933497f21bc1f8dbf","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 2ad8-f56e-7bc2-4948","material: 1821bab1914234ad","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 1","rebar-version: 0.7.1 (b0ac25447)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:79a10387a16d551668c4408716b135376480005f","dep absent .rebar/plan_review_moves.json","dep absent tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py"],"material_fingerprint":"1821bab1914234ad","merged_log_commit":"79a10387a16d551668c4408716b135376480005f","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784166537744750000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":1,"unsigned":12},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"aa3cc48ae795be34767a8f42ba9b7c556e6a2978588a05f78626080c377f94d8","event_uuid":"7725fdf3-a6c0-4a17-b6b8-b71666cda284","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784254193728369268-7725fdf3-a6c0-4a17-b6b8-b71666cda284"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-212_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"5c2eef83-9ceb-4320-ad07-f54047bb7399","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Pre-review grounding tightened the story against passes.load_move_registry, review_kernel.applicable_moves, and the real existing tests. Replaced the nonexistent regression test path, split the move definition and applicability into atomic ACs, and recorded the exact JSON contract plus experiment evidence.","timestamp":1784166196906906001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Retyped from story to task after the final scheduling audit: next-batch intentionally skips childless stories as planning containers. Scope, acceptance criteria, file impact, proving commands, dependencies, and title are unchanged; this ticket is the implementation leaf it was already planned to be.","timestamp":1784169407371521001}],"created_at":1784164044169718001,"deps":[{"link_uuid":"b2000f67-6a13-4975-84d5-065b90cd8ac0","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"3863-a783-b38f-4c8a"}],"description":"## Why\n\nA valid portability finding needs a productive Pass 4 response, but the proposed generic core move was rejected. The coaching behavior therefore belongs in project configuration and must remain invisible to unrelated criteria.\n\n## What\n\nAdd the project-specific `project-portability` coaching move and focused tests for loading, applicability, and deterministic rendering.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn scope:\n\n- `.rebar/plan_review_moves.json`\n- `tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py`\n- Pass 4 coaching for `project.portability` findings\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- generic core coaching moves\n- changes to built-in move definitions\n- Pass 1, Pass 2, or Pass 3 behavior\n- documentation and live criterion calibration\n\n## Approach\n\nUse the existing best-effort project move overlay proven by the fresh-worktree experiment. `.rebar/plan_review_moves.json` is a JSON object keyed by move id. Add exactly:\n\n- key `project-portability`\n- `name: restore rebar portability`\n- `template: Rework {subject} so it remains portable across supported rebar client shapes; keep project-specific behavior in project configuration or an explicit extension boundary.`\n- `applies_when: [project.portability]`\n\n`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/passes.py::load_move_registry` merges this file over a copy of the built-in registry with `strict=False`. `src/rebar/llm/review_kernel/coach.py::applicable_moves` admits the move only when its trigger intersects the surviving findings. `coach` then validates a bounded noun-phrase subject and renders the locked template deterministically. This project-owned composition is sufficient; no generic core move or kernel change is needed.\n\nThe established prior-art tests are `tests/unit/test_plan_review.py::test_load_move_registry_merges_project_extensions` and `tests/unit/test_plan_review.py::test_move_registry_matches_docs_table`. The parent epic experiment at `2026-07-16T00:50:08Z` proved the proposed id loads, remains excluded for trigger `F1`, becomes applicable for `project.portability`, and renders the locked sentence.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on the criterion-integration child because the move trigger must use the final activated criterion id.\n\n## Test Strategy\n\nLoad the real project move registry, query applicability with representative trigger sets, and render the move through the normal coaching path.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] The project registry loads a move keyed `project-portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k move_id`.\n- [ ] The loaded move name equals `restore rebar portability`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k move_name`.\n- [ ] The loaded move template equals the exact sentence specified in this plan. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k move_template`.\n- [ ] The loaded move declares only `project.portability` in `applies_when`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k move_trigger`.\n- [ ] The move is applicable for the trigger set `{project.portability}`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k applies_to_portability`.\n- [ ] The move is absent for an empty trigger set. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k ignores_empty_triggers`.\n- [ ] The move is absent for the unrelated trigger set `{F1}`. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k ignores_unrelated_findings`.\n- [ ] Rendering the subject `the Gerrit landing workflow` produces the exact locked sentence. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k deterministic_render`.\n- [ ] Loading the project move leaves the packaged `MOVE_REGISTRY` mapping unchanged. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py -k project_owned_only`.\n- [ ] Existing project move loading plus the built-in documentation-table invariant remain green. Prove with `.venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review.py -k move_registry`.\n","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":".rebar/plan_review_moves.json","reason":"define the project-scoped portability coaching move"},{"path":"tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py","reason":"verify move loading, applicability, and rendering"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","3863-a783-b38f-4c8a"],["parent","jira-reb-1003"]],"parent_id":"jira-reb-1003","parent_status_uuid":"bac50c0d-ecc6-490e-8553-8efb77939c87","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["plan-review","portability","coaching"],"ticket_id":"2ad8-f56e-7bc2-4948","ticket_type":"task","title":"Add scoped portability coaching","verify_commands":[{"command":".venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_project_portability_coaching.py","dd_id":"DD-1","dd_text":"Project coaching loading, applicability, isolation, and rendering are covered"},{"command":".venv/bin/pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review.py -k move_registry","dd_id":"DD-2","dd_text":"Existing project move loading and built-in documentation parity remain compatible"}]},"source_event_uuids":["7a859e14-f9c3-4239-a71d-4afcb654eb10","04e723f5-269f-468b-8731-c72fd1806ccc","20f0d271-19c0-4245-adba-c0b56f8c4b39","b2000f67-6a13-4975-84d5-065b90cd8ac0","3cdbcde3-b5cb-4380-98df-a4743e956cb3","b5e1e9db-0316-45ec-9577-0cdc30775f13","7c241297-0dc3-4b48-912a-83dfa4f1ebf6","8dd1e7b5-4912-4cd5-b60b-ea143d7ca32e","18b3b6bd-c81a-4c96-ae6d-eae2d62f947c","639f21f2-3893-4922-b2b9-0ae19b9a8277","bac50c0d-ecc6-490e-8553-8efb77939c87","9eccbb08-3f3e-4328-8015-ee330d77539a","7725fdf3-a6c0-4a17-b6b8-b71666cda284"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784254193728369269,"uuid":"a83134f2-3696-4aca-9cd8-9b9576740925"}